    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<div class=\"contentLayout2\"><style>[data-colorid=a9zps8c6kf]{color:#4c9aff} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=a9zps8c6kf]{color:#004eb3}</style>\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg\" width=\"760\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523361/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760464689&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=362\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/599523361/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760464689&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"611\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"599523374\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"599523361\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"4\" data-media-id=\"1ab0a284-0f2e-41f0-a1a3-35e4b57c8e0b\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523361/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760464689&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1280&amp;height=611 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523361/RenderMan_Fundamentals_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760464689&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=760&amp;height=362 1x\" /></span><p>Welcome to RenderMan Fundamentals, the official introductory training for Pixar's flagship renderer.</p><p>This page contains everything you need to install and learn the basics of RenderMan.</p><hr /><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"dbcc97e2-67c4-48a8-9741-578a52599cfe\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1456222991\"><div id=\"expander-control-1456222991\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Bump / Normal Mapping</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1456222991\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"70d3142d-12d3-4b73-bce4-e7b8d76dff05\" data-macro-id=\"ee9de45fcc893b9b29d30a12631adfef23fe0491773890595e25c73b737a57e2\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/471502555\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>In this lesson you&rsquo;ll learn how to use Bump and Normal maps within RenderMan correctly. We&rsquo;ll look at using the flexible per-lobe bump parameters for added creative possibilities.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"2d35f16b-6c19-4052-adfb-0ee4de36d4d6\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1323439346\"><div id=\"expander-control-1323439346\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Material Variation</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1323439346\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"c3bbb305-0279-45d8-bbcc-05bd858fb5e2\" data-macro-id=\"44fb301086519518dc1b07099005284ddd3c8144a379a54e7648e9c490619cd7\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/521360391\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>In this lesson, we're going to take a look at the incredibly versatile PxrVary node and how you can use it to add randomization to your materials. Download the Houdini file to follow along!</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"953e5131-6c56-465a-9739-11132ec222f5\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-47162600\"><div id=\"expander-control-47162600\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Procedural Grime</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-47162600\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"554f2488-f455-4529-aff5-d435c92e4741\" data-macro-id=\"cb4973873ce9cce5b3ff6424d878e4e4563a7d5a1fb53599521f65cec7f3f602\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/521880422\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>In this lesson, learn how to create realistic procedural dirt, dust, and grime using the PxrDirt &amp; PxrCurvature nodes.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"616e6751-9d12-48f9-a080-1016d4449824\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1314290827\"><div id=\"expander-control-1314290827\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Triplanar Mapping</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1314290827\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"5d1e65a0-b63c-42c8-b3a4-67fd59a4325c\" data-macro-id=\"8c57f8ef647486013570232aca894716b75ad1120e45a018a8054ca8d18b09b4\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/521895290\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>This lesson will give you the fundamental understanding of how to get beautiful and seamless texture maps on your models by using the PxrRoundCube &amp; PxrMultiTexture nodes.</p></div></div><div class=\"expand-container conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-layout=\"wide\" data-macro-id=\"e4f22984-fc0a-4156-ac5b-32f02d792a57\" data-macro-name=\"expand\" id=\"expander-1706752967\"><div id=\"expander-control-1706752967\" class=\"expand-control\"><span class=\"expand-control-icon icon\">&nbsp;</span><span class=\"expand-control-text\">Custom Outputs</span></div><div id=\"expander-content-1706752967\" class=\"expand-content expand-hidden\"><iframe allowfullscreen=\"\" allowtransparency=\"true\" class=\"fullscreen-video-iframe conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"false\" data-layout=\"default\" data-local-id=\"207062ee-ba1d-4cf9-b44f-1ce091934dc9\" data-macro-id=\"2920455a888fd08dbd5e039206a3daa9918cd8077b5b667424acf8c8dd56bd3f\" data-macro-name=\"widget\" frameborder=\"0\" height=\"540\" mozallowfullscreen=\"\" src=\"https://player.vimeo.com/video/521908120\" style=\"border:none; margin:1em 0em;\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"\" width=\"960\">\n</iframe>\n\n<p>Learn how the PxrTee node is capable of outputting any pattern to an AOV and the advantages it brings to your compositing and look-dev workflow.</p></div></div><p /><hr /><h3 id=\"R.F.-Patterns-NextSteps\"><span data-colorid=\"a9zps8c6kf\">Next Steps</span></h3><p>Nice &hellip; that&rsquo;s the shading part of the RenderMan Fundamentals complete.<br />Now, let&rsquo;s move onto looking at some lighting!</p><p /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout two-equal\" data-layout=\"two-equal\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<a href=\"/wiki/spaces/RU/pages/600113153/R.F.+-+Materials+-+Lama\" data-linked-resource-id=\"600113153\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-left-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-left\" alt=\"previousLesson.png\" width=\"200\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523361/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760464689&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=200&amp;height=46\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/599523361/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760464689&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"67\" data-width=\"286\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"599523377\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"previousLesson.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"599523361\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"4\" data-media-id=\"d32134ca-e7ce-466e-aec9-5bc5e567802e\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/599523361/previousLesson.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1757760464689&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=286&amp;height=67 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/